,"Germanized or Americanized form of Czech, Slovak, Croatian, and Slovenian <b>Valter</b> and Czech <b>Valtr</b>: from the personal name <i>Valter</i>, <i>Valtr</i>, of ancient Germanic origin (see 1 above)."],"variants":[{"name":"Walthers","meanings":["German: patronymic from the personal name <i>Walther</i> (see   Walter  )."]},{"name":"McQuate","meanings":["Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Uait</b> ‘son of <i>Uat</i>’, Gaelic form of the personal name <i>Wat</i>, a short form of   Walter  . Compare the Irish form   McQuaid  ."]},{"name":"Waltke","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Jurgen, Wilhelmina.","German: from a pet form of any of the ancient Germanic personal names formed with Old High German <i>waltan</i> ‘to rule’ as the first element, as in   Walter  ."]},{"name":"McWaters","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Uaitéir</b>, a patronymic from a Gaelicized form of the personal name   Walter  , with excrescent English <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Wahler","meanings":["German:","from the personal name <i>Wol(d)er</i>, Low German form of   Walter  .","habitational name for someone from any of various places called Wahl, Wahle, or Wahlen."]},{"name":"McWalter","meanings":["Irish and Scottish: from Gaelic <b>Mac Uaitéir</b> ‘son of   Walter  ’."]},{"name":"Walters","meanings":["English: variant of   Walter  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","German: patronymic from   Walter  ."]},{"name":"McQuaid","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Colum, Nuala.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Uaid</b> ‘son of <i>Uad</i>’, Gaelic form of the personal name <i>Wat</i>, a short form of   Walter  . Compare the Scottish form   McQuate  ."]},{"name":"Walther","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Hans, Erwin, Wolfgang, Otto, Gerhard, Gunter, Heinz, Klaus, Konrad, Bernd, Bernhard.","German, Dutch, Swedish, and Danish: variant of   Walter  ."]},{"name":"Lauter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Ernst, Erwin, Kurt, Sigismund, Wolf.","German: topographic name and habitational name, from a common stream name meaning ‘clear’, from Middle High German <i>hlutra</i>, or from any of the places called Lauter or Lauta (Saxony). This surname is also found in France (Alsace and Lorraine) and some other European countries.","Germanized or Americanized form of Slovenian <b>Lavtar</b> or its Croatized and rare Slovenian variant <b>Lautar</b>: from a dialect variant of the personal name <i>Valter</i> (see   Walter  )."]}]},{"name":"Aliz","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant of   Alex  , used only as a feminine name. Its formation has probably been influenced by   Alice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Aliz Walter was born about 1118, in England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Hervey Walter and Mrs. Hervey Walter. She married Magnus de Heaton II before 1137, in Grimsargh, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons."},"et":{"Abt 1118–":"umbes 1118–Surnud","1118–Female":"1118–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1115–1180":"1115–1180","1139–1180":"1139–1180","1141–Male":"1141–Surnud","1145–Male":"1145–Surnud","–1118":"–1118","–Female":"Surnud","1118":"1118","1139":"1139","before 1137":"enne 1137","1159":"1159","1115":"1115","1145":"1145","1141":"1141","before 1118":"enne 1118","Abt 1118":"umbes 1118","1180":"1180","Of England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Grimsargh, Lancashire, England":"Grimsargh, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Grimsargh, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Grimsargh, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Mersham, Grimsargh, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Grimsargh, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1118–":"noin 1118–Kuollut","1118–Female":"1118–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1115–1180":"1115–1180","11